                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><expan><abbr>Θ</abbr><ex>εοῖς</ex></expan> <supplied reason="lost"><expan><abbr>κ</abbr><ex>αταχθονίοις</ex></expan></supplied>
                    <lb n="2"/><persName type="attested"><name>Κρασσ<unclear>ι</unclear></name></persName><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
                    <lb n="3"/>ἔζησε<supplied reason="lost">ν</supplied> <supplied reason="lost">ἔτη</supplied> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
                </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus" resp="#JP">
                <listApp>
                    <app>
                        <note>Text based upon photograph in publication</note>
                    </app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#JP">
                <p>To the spirits of the underword. Krassi[--] lived [--] years [---]</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Names in 'Krassi-' are surprisingly rare. Κρασσίκιος, Κρασσίων and the Latin cognomen Crassipes are almost the only forms attested.</p>
            </div>
